{{Han compound|人|言|ls=ic|t1=person|t2=word}} – a person's (truthful) words.

===Etymology===
Possibly derived from {{och-l|[[允]]}} (if minimally reconstructed as *''winʔ'') {{zh-ref|(Schuessler, 2007)}}

Alternatively, {{zh-ref|Baxter & Sagart (2012)}} reconstruct *''s-niŋ-s'' and suggest a derivation, albeit uncertain, from {{och-l|仁|tr=niŋ}} with valency-increasing prefix ''s-''; as apparently "while 仁 rén means 'kindness' as a property of a single person, when 信 xìn is used, it refers to a quality directed to another person"

